{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877572730,"sessionID":"ses_28573097fffenOKKsxrsqAW5XT","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8d4343001STjE15QSmbga09","messageID":"msg_d7a8d326c001qzK2YSIjRhRt58","sessionID":"ses_28573097fffenOKKsxrsqAW5XT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_4296c046bca14af490b9543e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This AR implements 12 GitHub Actions workflows to automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-034\n10: - **Module**: `.github`\n11: - **Language**: `YAML`\n12: - **Size**: L\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Scenario: Build Verification\n17: \n18: ### AR-034-001: Docker build in CI\n19: \n20: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n21: - **WHEN** the \"Agentcube CI Workflow\" (main.yml) runs\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n23: - **AND** SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## Scenario: Lint and Code Quality\n28: \n29: ### AR-034-002: Go lint on changed Go code\n30: \n31: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n32: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow (lint.yml) runs\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint` using golangci-lint\n34: \n35: ### AR-034-003: Python lint with Ruff\n36: \n37: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`\n38: - **WHEN** the Python Lint job runs with Python `3.10`\n39: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install ruff` and run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n40: \n41: ### AR-034-004: Spelling check with codespell\n42: \n43: - **GIVEN** checkout complete on a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n44: - **WHEN** the Codespell workflow runs\n45: - **THEN** it SHALL temporarily backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json` at repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n46: - **AND** SHALL use `pip install codespell` and run codespell with `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on `.`\n47: - **AND** SHALL restore backed-up files after check completes\n48: \n49: ### AR-034-005: Copyright header check\n50: \n51: - **GIVEN** path filter marks `copyright` (all paths minus exclusions for `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**`)\n52: - **WHEN** the Copyright Check workflow runs\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (`sponge`), run `make gen-copyright`, and execute `git diff --exit-code`\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Scenario: Code Generation\n58: \n59: ### AR-034-006: Code generation verification\n60: \n61: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n62: - **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs with Go `1.24.4`\n63: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make gen-check` which executes `make gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## Scenario: Testing\n68: \n69: ### AR-034-007: Go test coverage reporting\n70: \n71: - **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding some media/docs per workflow) on a pull request or merge group\n72: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n74: - **AND** SHALL upload `coverage.out` as an artifact\n75: - **AND** SHALL optionally upload to Codecov when `CODECOV_TOKEN` is present\n76: \n77: ### AR-034-008: End-to-end testing on Kind\n78: \n79: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n80: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow (e2e.yml) runs\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n82: - **AND** SHALL install Kind tool v0.30.0 using `helm/kind-action@v1` with `install_only: true`\n83: - **AND** SHALL run `make e2e` with Go `1.23`\n84: - **AND** SHALL upload `e2e-logs/` directory on failure\n85: - **AND** SHALL always run `make e2e-clean` to clean up resources\n86: \n87: ### AR-034-009: Python SDK unit tests\n88: \n89: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `sdk-python/**`\n90: - **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests job runs with Python `3.12` in `sdk-python/`\n91: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install pytest`\n92: - **AND** SHALL `pip install -e .` (editable install)\n93: - **AND** SHALL run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## Scenario: Release and Publication\n98: \n99: ### AR-034-010: Release image publication\n100: \n101: - **GIVEN** a `push` event to `main` branch or semantic version tags (`v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*`)\n102: - **WHEN** the Build and Push Release Images workflow runs\n103: - **THEN** it SHALL determine `TAG` - if `github.ref_type` is `tag`, `TAG` SHALL be `github.ref_name`; otherwise `TAG` SHALL be `latest`\n104: - **AND** SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` with `GITHUB_TOKEN`\n105: - **AND** SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push` for workloadmanager, `docker-buildx-push-router` for router, and `docker-buildx-push-picod` for picod\n106: - **AND** SHALL set `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and per-image `*_IMAGE=<name>:${TAG}`\n107: \n108: ### AR-034-011: Dify plugin publish\n109: \n110: - **GIVEN** a push event with tags matching `dify-plugin/v*`\n111: - **WHEN** the Dify Plugin Publish workflow runs\n112: - **THEN** it SHALL download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6 and install `yq`\n113: - **AND** SHALL read `manifest.yaml` and package the plugin as `.difypkg`\n114: - **AND** SHALL checkout `author/dify-plugins` repository with token\n115: - **AND** SHALL move `.difypkg` to the repository\n116: - **AND** SHALL create a branch, commit, push, and create a PR to `langgenius/dify-plugins`\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## Scenario: Workflow Automation\n121: \n122: ### AR-034-012: First-time contributor workflow approval\n123: \n124: - **GIVEN** a `pull_request_target` event with types `labeled` or `synchronize` on `main` or `release-**` branches\n125: - **WHEN** a contributor is not first-time (more than one PR merged) or PR has `ok-to-test` label\n126: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required`\n127: - **AND** SHALL call `approveWorkflowRun` for each pending run\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ## References\n132: \n133: - AgentCube proposal: `changes/AR-034/proposal.md`\n134: - CI/CD design: `ci-cd/design.md`\n135: - CI/CD spec: `ci-cd/spec.md`\n136: - GitHub Actions documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/actions\n137: \n138: (End of file)\n\n(End of file - total 138 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis AR implements 12 GitHub Actions workflows to automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-034\n- **Module**: `.github`\n- **Language**: `YAML`\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Build Verification\n\n### AR-034-001: Docker build in CI\n\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775877572705,"end":1775877572725}}}}
